OL,3,CContractor fined after forestry
OL,4,Cworker, 61, left paralysed by falling
OL,5,Ctree
OL,7,FA contractor from Dorset has been
OL,8,Ffined after a tree fell onto a
OL,9,Fforestry worker and left him with life-
OL,10,Fchanging injuries.
OL,12,FThe 61-year-old man is now paralysed
OL,13,Ffrom the stomach down after the 21-
OL,14,Fmetre ash tree landed on top of him at
OL,15,FThe Fonthill Estate in Salisbury,
OL,16,FWiltshire, on 12 January 2022.
OL,18,FGerald Hayward, who had been
OL,19,Fcontracted as part of an ash dieback
OL,20,Fclearance programme, had been cutting
OL,21,Fthe tree before it fell.
